description:
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;span&gt;Band 6 - Local Security Management Specialist &lt;/span&gt; &lt;span&gt;flexible and/or full time hours considered&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;An opportunity has arisen for a forward thinking individual to join the Local Security Management Team, with in the Risk Management Department. The successful post holder will be responsible for providing specialist advice, support and will liaise with both internal and external stakeholders, for example staff who are the victims of assault and the police. The post holder will also work collaboratively with other teams and services within the Trust to provide a coordinated approach to the security management service that we deliver in order to support staff and manage the Trusts Security Framework.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Work base: The role is based at the Trust headquarters in Runwell, Essex; but you must be able to travel to any of the Trusts units to undertake the role should this be required. The Trust geography spans Bedfordshire, Essex and Suffolk areas.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;As part of the interview process the candidates will be expected to prepare a management report (maximum 4 sides of A4) and share at the interview (please also email copy across). The report must be in a style appropriate for consideration by the leadership team of the Trust. Candidates will be required to present a verbal summary of the written report to the interview panel as if they were presenting it to a committee. Candidates should assume that they have 8 minutes presentation time with 5 minutes allowed for discussion and questions. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The outline brief for the report is as follows : As you will be aware that from the 1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;st&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; April 2017 NHS Project no longer governs the LSMS agenda; using your knowledge, skills and experience advise what the implications for EPUT are and what the priorities are in the short, medium and long term.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The interviews will be held via Microsoft Teams only&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Closing date for applications will be 19th November&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Interviews to be held on 4th December&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;EPUT are looking for motivated staff who shares our Trust values of Open, Compassionate and Empowering. In return, EPUT can offer you a range of benefits and development including;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Season Ticket Loans&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NHS discounts for staff&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent Training facilities and opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Buying and Selling annual leave scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The opportunity to work bank shifts and expand knowledge and experience in other areas&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Salary Sacrifice schemes including lease cars and Cycle to Work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name Jo Englefield Email address j.englefield@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
